## Lab Environment

| Component | Technology |
|-----------|------------|
| **OS** | Windows Server 2025 Standard |
| **Service** | Active Directory Domain Services (AD DS) |
| **Domain** | practicelab.com |
| **Locations** | 2 (London, Venice) |
| **Departments** | 4 (IT & HR per location) |
| **Tools** | Active Directory Users & Computers, Group Policy Management Console |
| **Virtualization** | Oracle VirtualBox |

---

## What I Learned

### Technical Insights
- **OU design impacts everything:** Structure determines GPO inheritance and delegation possibilities
- **Group scope matters:** Global for single-domain, Universal for cross-domain scenarios
- **Computer vs User configuration:** Computer policies apply regardless of who logs in
- **Security vs Distribution groups:** Only Security groups can assign permissions

### Practical Skills
- Creating realistic organizational structures in AD
- Applying security policies that balance protection with usability
- Troubleshooting GPO application and inheritance
- Documenting infrastructure decisions

### Professional Development
- How to translate business requirements into technical controls
- Importance of least privilege in real-world scenarios
- Value of clear naming conventions and organizational standards


**Advanced goals:**
- [ ] Integrate with Azure AD Connect
- [ ] Set up AD Certificate Services (PKI)
- [ ] Configure Active Directory Federation Services (AD FS)
- [ ] Implement tiered administrative model

